---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AgentPlayground from '../components/islands/AgentPlayground';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="ReAct Playground — Thomas Abraham"
  description="Live ReAct tool-use playground — submit a query and watch the agent reason, call tools, observe results, and synthesise an answer."
>
  <!-- Header -->
  <div class="mb-10">
    <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-agent-500 bg-agent-900/30 border border-agent-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full mb-4 font-mono">
      <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-agent-500 rounded-full animate-pulse"></span>
      Playground · Live ReAct Tool-Use
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Agent Playground</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
      Trigger a tool-use event live. The agent decides which tools to call, in what order — every
      <span class="text-blue-400 font-mono">thought</span>,
      <span class="text-yellow-400 font-mono">action</span>, and
      <span class="text-gray-300 font-mono">observation</span> streams in over SSE
      as it happens.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Playground island -->
  <AgentPlayground client:load />

  <!-- Tech notes -->
  <section class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-800">
    <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">How it works</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
      <div class="bg-gray-900/40 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-white font-medium mb-1">ReAct loop</p>
        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          Classic ReAct: <span class="font-mono text-blue-400">thought</span> →
          <span class="font-mono text-yellow-400">action</span> (tool call) →
          <span class="font-mono text-gray-400">observation</span> → repeat → final answer.
          Each step streams over Server-Sent Events so the trace renders live.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-900/40 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-white font-medium mb-1">Tools available</p>
        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          The agent has a small registry — current weather, local time, and a
          portfolio-project recommender. It picks what to call based on the query;
          you can see the full call graph in the live trace.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-900/40 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-white font-medium mb-1">Mock vs. real mode</p>
        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          The current planner is a small heuristic (keyword → tool plan); the real-mode
          swap is a single LLM call with the tool registry passed as a system prompt.
          Tool implementations swap from canned data to OpenWeather + request-header
          geolocation + pgvector search.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-900/40 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-white font-medium mb-1">Rate limiting</p>
        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          The endpoint is capped at 10 runs per 10 minutes per visitor to keep the
          demo cheap and prevent abuse. The input is also length-limited (500 chars)
          and validated server-side before any tool is invoked.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
